    "is_free": false,
    "description": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >In the beginning was chess, and chess was good. Then chess got too good, and thus chess became less good. But then chess got Hexagon, and harmony ensued.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >This is a pretty polished lean implementation of Władysław Gliński's Hexagonal Chess. The game itself is pretty old (~75 years) and got lost to time with its creator's death. It's worth another life.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >It's similar to usual chess we all know &amp; love, but it uses hexes instead of default square grid. That changes the whole meta, invalidating tons of pre-existing memorized plays &amp; allowing for actually experiencing the game anew.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Includes:</p><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Hotseat (local multiplayer)</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Playing against AI</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Online multiplayer with matchmaking</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Multiple beautiful maps to play on</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Interactive game chat</p></li></ul>",
